'''''Baseball Fanatic''''' is a 1986 video game published by [[Performing Arts Software]].

==Gameplay==
''Baseball Fanatic'' is a game in which the player can choose from five different levels of play which affect the offensive production of the players.<ref name="CGW36"/>

==Reception==
Johnny Wilson reviewed the game for ''[[Computer Gaming World]]'', and stated that "Unlike most statistical games, the game plays one pitch at a time, which allows you to mix up your pitches and attempt to fool each batter."<ref name="CGW36">{{cite magazine |last=Wilson |first=Johnny |title=Baseball Fever |magazine=Computer Gaming World |date=April 1987 |volume=1 |issue=36 |pages=43â€“44}}</ref>

